\frac{d y} {dx} + \frac{1}{t}y=3 \cos(2t)
y' + p(t)y=g(t)
(1+t^2)\,y'+4\,t\,y'=(1+(t^2)^{-2})
t\,y' + 2\,y=\sin t
dy/dt
t y' + y = 3 t \cos{2 t}
\frac{d}{dt} (t y) = 3 t \cos{2 t}
t y(t) = 3 \int dt \, t \, \cos{2 t} = \frac{3}{2} t \sin{2 t} - \frac{3}{2} \int dt \, \sin{2 t} 
y(t) =  \frac{3}{2} \sin{2 t} + \frac{3}{4} \frac{\cos{2 t} + C}{t} 
